HEADWORD: Overshade
<hw>O`ver*shade`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>ofersceadwian</ets>. See <er>Over</er>, and <er>Shade</er>, and cf.
<er>Overshadow</er>.]</ety> <def>To cover with shade; to render dark or
gloomy; to overshadow.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

